  <exploration xml:id="PA-8-4">
    <introduction>
      <p>
    Let 
    <me>
      T(x) = 3 - x + \frac{1}{3}x^2 - \frac{1}{9}x^3 + \cdots + 3 \cdot \left(- \frac{1}{3} \right)^n x^n + \cdots
    </me>.
  </p>
      <p/>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="PA-8-4-task-0">
      <statement>
        <p>
          Explain why <m>T(x)</m> is a geometric series and identify the values of <m>a</m> and <m>r</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <hint/>
       
       
    </task>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="PA-8-4-task-1">
      <statement>
        <p>
          Recall that the sum of an infinite geometric series with first term <m>a</m> and constant ratio <m>r</m> is <m>S = \frac{1}{1-r}</m>, provided <m>|r| \lt 1</m>.  Use this result to find a single fraction that represents the value of <m>T(x)</m>.  For which values of <m>x</m> is this representation valid?
        </p>
      </statement>
      <hint/>
       
       
    </task>
